01:51:49,660 --> 01:51:51,955
Who are you calling now?

2211
01:51:52,038 --> 01:51:55,835
You called
that number not ten minutes ago.

2212
01:51:55,918 --> 01:51:57,170
Hello, Mr. Connell.

2213
01:51:57,254 --> 01:51:58,380
Have you seen him yet?

2214
01:51:58,462 --> 01:51:59,214
Now listen, Ann.

2215
01:51:59,297 --> 01:52:01,883
He can't possibly get
in without our seeing him.

2216
01:52:01,968 --> 01:52:04,137
I'm watching the side
door and the Colonel's out front,

2217
01:52:04,221 --> 01:52:06,307
so stop worrying.

2218
01:52:06,391 --> 01:52:07,724
Oh, thank you.

2219
01:52:15,403 --> 01:52:16,320
Why, Ann!

2220
01:52:16,404 --> 01:52:19,157
Ann, don't be foolish.

2221
01:52:21,995 --> 01:52:23,622
If this isn't the craziest, the battiest,

2222
01:52:23,706 --> 01:52:26,209
the looniest wild
goose chase I ever heard of.

2223
01:52:26,293 --> 01:52:27,043
Oh, shut up, Bert.

2224
01:52:27,127 --> 01:52:28,169
Sourpuss is right.

2225
01:52:28,254 --> 01:52:30,172
Yeah, well if he is, I'm a banana split.

2226
01:52:30,256 --> 01:52:31,842
That man's gonna be on that roof.

2227
01:52:31,925 --> 01:52:33,886
Don't ask me how I know, I just know,

2228
01:52:33,970 --> 01:52:35,138
and you know it as well as I do.

2229
01:52:35,221 --> 01:52:37,349
Sure, sure, I'd like
to believe in fairy tales,

2230
01:52:37,433 --> 01:52:39,977
but a guy that's a fake
isn't gonna jump off any roof.

2231
01:52:40,061 --> 01:52:41,980
I don't think he was
any fake, not with that face,

2232
01:52:42,062 --> 01:52:44,442
and any way,
what he stood for wasn't a fake.

2233
01:52:44,525 --> 01:52:46,193
Okay, honey, okay.

2234
01:53:06,430 --> 01:53:08,642
Elevators ain't runnin'.

2235
01:53:08,725 --> 01:53:09,768
Colonel.

2236
01:53:09,851 --> 01:53:11,604
You shouldn't've got out of bed, Miss.

2237
01:53:11,687 --> 01:53:12,647
Has he been here?

2238
01:53:12,729 --> 01:53:13,481
No.

2239
01:53:13,564 --> 01:53:14,315
Have you seen him?

2240
01:53:14,399 --> 01:53:15,150
I ain't seen him for a week.

2241
01:53:15,233 --> 01:53:15,984
Where's Connell?

2242
01:53:16,068 --> 01:53:16,903
He's watching the other door.

2243
01:53:16,986 --> 01:53:19,490
Oh, gee, you're swell.

2244
01:53:24,662 --> 01:53:25,873
No sense in going up there.

2245
01:53:25,957 --> 01:53:26,791
I been here for hours.

2246
01:53:26,874 --> 01:53:27,625
He ain't here.

2247
01:53:27,707 --> 01:53:29,168
Let me go, will ya?

2248
01:53:33,717 --> 01:53:34,718
Now, that's crazy.

2249
01:53:34,802 --> 01:53:36,011
It's 14 floors.

2250
01:54:19,195 --> 01:54:20,739
It's as far as the elevator goes.

2251
01:54:20,822 --> 01:54:22,491
We gotta walk up to the tower.

2252
01:55:13,560 --> 01:55:15,270
That tramp is
probably full of Christmas cheer

2253
01:55:15,354 --> 01:55:16,981
and asleep in some flophouse.

2254
01:55:17,065 --> 01:55:17,816
Let's go.

2255
01:55:17,898 --> 01:55:20,319
I've got to decorate my tree.

2256
01:55:31,960 --> 01:55:33,462
Well, I give up.

2257
01:55:34,421 --> 01:55:35,631
I don't what gave us the idea

2258
01:55:35,714 --> 01:55:38,093
he'd attempt anything like this.

2259
01:55:38,176 --> 01:55:39,345
I guess you're right.

2260
01:55:39,428 --> 01:55:41,388
I'm afraid the joke's on us.

2261
01:55:41,473 --> 01:55:42,224
Let's go.

2262
01:55:42,307 --> 01:55:44,394
I hope nobody finds out we've been here.

2263
01:57:30,244 --> 01:57:32,289
I wouldn't do that if I were you, John.

2264
01:57:44,264 --> 01:57:46,016
It'll do you no good.

2265
01:57:46,892 --> 01:57:50,439
The Mayor has policemen
downstairs with instructions

2266
01:57:50,522 --> 01:57:52,107
to remove all marks of identification

2267
01:57:52,189 --> 01:57:53,526
you may have on your person.

2268
01:57:55,070 --> 01:57:57,030
You'll be buried in Potter's Field,

2269
01:57:57,114 --> 01:57:58,825
and you'll have accomplished nothing.

2270
01:58:09,882 --> 01:58:12,051
I've taken care of that.

2271
01:58:13,053 --> 01:58:17,809
I've already mailed
a copy of this letter to Mr. Connell.

2272
01:58:19,102 --> 01:58:21,105
John, why don't
you forget this foolishness?

2273
01:58:21,189 --> 01:58:22,731
Stop right where you are, Mr. Norton,

2274
01:58:22,815 --> 01:58:25,027
if you don't want to go overboard with me.

2275
01:58:29,575 --> 01:58:31,786
I'm glad you gentlemen are here.

2276
01:58:33,954 --> 01:58:37,418
You killed
the John Doe movement, all right,

2277
01:58:37,502 --> 01:58:41,174
but you're gonna
see it born all over again.

2278
01:58:47,807 --> 01:58:49,643
Now, take a good look, Mr. Norton.

2279
01:58:51,020 --> 01:58:51,854
John!

2280
01:58:52,981 --> 01:58:53,816
John!

2281
01:58:54,733 --> 01:58:57,028
Oh, John, don't do it!

2282
01:58:57,112 --> 01:58:59,782
I won't let you.
I love you, darling.

2283
01:58:59,865 --> 01:59:03,454
Oh, please, please don't give up.

2284
01:59:03,538 --> 01:59:05,206
We'll start all over again.

2285
01:59:05,289 --> 01:59:06,582
Just you and I.

2286
01:59:06,667 --> 01:59:07,501
It isn't too late.

2287
01:59:07,584 --> 01:59:10,964
The John Doe movement isn't dead yet.

2288
01:59:11,047 --> 01:59:13,258
You see, John, it isn't
dead or they wouldn't be here.

2289
01:59:13,342 --> 01:59:14,928
It's alive in them.

2290
01:59:15,011 --> 01:59:17,388
They kept it alive by being afraid of it.

2291
01:59:17,472 --> 01:59:19,267
That's why they came up here.

2292
01:59:19,349 --> 01:59:22,770
Oh, darling, sure
it should have been killed.

2293
01:59:22,855 --> 01:59:25,817
It was dishonest,
but we can start clean now,

2294
01:59:25,900 --> 01:59:27,361
just you and I.

2295
01:59:27,445 --> 01:59:28,864
It'll grow, John, and it'll grow big

2296
01:59:28,947 --> 01:59:31,783
because it'll be honest this time.

2297
01:59:32,910 --> 01:59:37,917
Oh, John, if it's worth
dying for, it's worth living for.

2298
01:59:38,209 --> 01:59:39,878
Oh, please, John!

2299
01:59:40,588 --> 01:59:44,843
Oh, oh please!

2300
01:59:44,925 --> 01:59:47,513
Please God, help me!

2301
01:59:49,891 --> 01:59:50,684
John!

2302
01:59:51,268 --> 01:59:52,520
John, look at me!

2303
01:59:53,104 --> 01:59:55,316
You want to be honest, don't you?

2304
01:59:55,398 --> 01:59:58,111
You don't have to die to
keep the John Doe idea alive.

2305
01:59:58,195 --> 02:00:02,033
Someone already died for
that once, the first John Doe,

2306
02:00:02,783 --> 02:00:05,579
and He's kept that idea
alive for nearly 2,000 years.

2307
02:00:05,914 --> 02:00:08,249
It was He who kept
it alive in them, and He'll go on

2308
02:00:08,333 --> 02:00:10,461
keeping it alive forever and always.

2309
02:00:11,003 --> 02:00:12,589
For every John Doe
movement these men kill,

2310
02:00:12,672 --> 02:00:14,425
a new one will be born.

2311
02:00:15,134 --> 02:00:16,927
That's why those bells are ringing, John.

2312
02:00:17,177 --> 02:00:18,513
They're calling to us.

2313
02:00:18,597 --> 02:00:21,976
Not to give up, but keep
on fighting, to keep on pitching.

2314
02:00:22,059 --> 02:00:24,188
Oh, don't you see, darling?

2315
02:00:24,271 --> 02:00:26,565
This is no time to give up.

2316
02:00:26,650 --> 02:00:28,778
You and I John, we, oh no!

2317
02:00:30,196 --> 02:00:32,824
Oh, no! No, John!

2318
02:00:32,908 --> 02:00:35,286
If you die, I want to die, too.

2319
02:00:35,620 --> 02:00:38,040
Oh. Oh, I love you.

2320
02:00:52,851 --> 02:00:58,776
Mr. Doe, you don't have to...
we're with you, Mr. Doe.

2321
02:00:58,859 --> 02:01:01,071
We just lost
our heads and acted like a mob.

2322
02:01:01,196 --> 02:01:04,742
What Bert's trying to say
is that we need you, Mr. Doe.

2323
02:01:04,826 --> 02:01:05,578
There were a lot of us

2324
02:01:05,661 --> 02:01:07,162
that didn't believe what that man said.

2325
02:01:07,954 --> 02:01:10,125
We were going to start
up our John Doe Club again,

2326
02:01:10,208 --> 02:01:12,420
whether we saw
you or not, weren't we, Bert?

2327
02:01:12,503 --> 02:01:13,337
And there were a lot of others

2328
02:01:13,420 --> 02:01:15,006
there were gonna do the same thing.

2329
02:01:15,090 --> 02:01:16,383
Well, Mr. Sourpuss even got a letter

2330
02:01:16,466 --> 02:01:18,011
from his cousin in Toledo.

2331
02:01:18,094 --> 02:01:19,304
I got it right here, Mr. Doe.

2332
02:01:19,387 --> 02:01:22,391
Only, it'd be a lot easier with you.

2333
02:01:22,474 --> 02:01:27,481
Please, please come with us, Mr. Doe.

2334
02:01:53,475 --> 02:01:54,518
Long John!

2335
02:01:54,602 --> 02:01:56,270
Mr. Doe!

2336
02:01:56,354 --> 02:01:57,564
Here, we'll help you with her.

2337
02:01:57,648 --> 02:01:58,398
She'll be all right.

2338
02:01:58,481 --> 02:02:01,444
Mr. Doe,
take her right down to the car.

2339
02:02:01,527 --> 02:02:03,405
We got a car right down there.

2340
02:02:03,489 --> 02:02:05,115
There you are, Norton, the people!

2341
02:02:05,199 --> 02:02:06,368
Try and lick that!

